message.text:
It has been three years since the Great East Japan Earthquake struck, bringing massive damage to the extensive areas in Japan, especially to the Tohoku region. The Japan Foundation would like to once again express our deep sympathy to those who have been enduring tremendous hardships from the disaster. 
東北地方を中心とする広い範囲に甚大な被害をもたらした東日本大震災から今日で３年を迎えます。今もなお、被災により様々な困難に直面されている方々に、あらためてお見舞いを申し上げます。

The Japan Foundation has implemented wide-ranging cultural programs intensively, sending messages from post-quake Japan to the globe. Through these programs, we have found various forms of ties being present between the devastated areas and international communities across the globe. Also, there has been a variety of new exchange networks created in the wake of the earthquake. 
With the hope of encouraging those who have suffered from the disaster and of playing a role in taking steps toward recovery, we will continuously support and promote exchanges between Japan, including the disaster-stricken areas, and all over the world. 
国際交流基金は、震災後の日本からのメッセージを、文化を通して世界各地に向けて集中的に発信してまいりました。これらの過程で、被災地と海外との間には、さまざまな結びつきがあることに気付かされました。また、震災を契機に生まれた交流の萌芽もあちこちに見られました。
被災地の現場で生まれ、営まれる交流を支援することで、被災地の人々を励まし、復興への歩みを支える活力になればという思いで、国際交流基金は、今後も被災地をはじめ日本と海外との文化交流に邁進してまいります。

■をちこちMagazine　特集040: 震災で生まれた交流の芽を育てる
http://www.wochikochi.jp/

Dear friends all over the world:

We appreciate your continued friendship and always wish you every happiness as well!

World×Friends＝The Japan Foundation.

message.text:
Drama "Carnation" to be aired in Myanmar's first commercial broadcaster!
Based on the true life story of Ayako Koshino, whose three daughters became internationally acclaimed fashion designers, the story depicts women's independence, cutting edge fashion, and growth as a family. 
ミャンマー初の民放テレビでNHKドラマ「カーネーション」を放送開始！
http://www.jpf.go.jp/e/culture/new/1402/02-06.html
©NHK
